history.content: Yes, it is true. I think you can figure out the answer to your 2nd question without additional help.

Hi All,

I really wanted to take CS 70 and a non EECS class in which attendance is mandatory. I thought I would be able to enrol in both of them as CS70 does not require attendance (my non EECS class clashes with CS70 lecture) but when I was browsing classes.berkeley.edu I saw that CS70 does not allow time conflicts. 

Is this true? And if so, is there no way I can enrol in both classes? 

Thanks!

Screenshot of classes.berkeley.edu below for reference
